{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ef8eeb7d-c89a-47b0-9ce8-17935f059104","content":"This project uses **`packages.config`** — the legacy NuGet package format. Central Package Management (CPM) requires **PackageReference** format, which `packages.config` projects don't support.\n\n**You need to migrate from `packages.config` to `PackageReference` first** before CPM can be enabled. You can do this in Visual Studio:\n\n1. **Right-click** `packages.config` in Solution Explorer → **Migrate packages.config to PackageReference**\n2. Review and confirm the migration\n3. Then re-run the CPM conversion\n\nAlternatively, if you're targeting .NET Framework 4.8 and can move to SDK-style projects, update the `.csproj` to SDK format which uses `PackageReference` by default.\n\nWould you like me to manually convert this project to SDK-style with `PackageReference`, after which I can apply CPM?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"28d5a293-53b4-4547-82cd-75cd2b99cba9","outputTokens":203,"requestId":"8417:2582EE:1176F1:15B25C:69F54AD7"},"id":"305b35e7-c165-4dc2-aa49-1a01b1d0dfe7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:52:44.384Z","parentId":"8b42629d-db27-4ea8-8c1f-7bc79de45665"}
